article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 108, Hendrix College 65
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- LaQuentin Miles scored 17 points Tuesday night, leading seven Central Arkansas players in double figures and the Bears rolled past Hendrix College 108-65. Robert Crawford and Ryan Williams had 14 points apiece for the Bears (1-1), while Jarvis Garner and DeShone McClure scored 12, Daouda Berete 11 and Jordan Harks 10. Jaren Riley led all scorers with 18 points for Hendrix, which plays in Division III and counted this game as an exhibition. Central Arkansas is coming off a loss to Arizona State on Saturday. The crosstown rivals have met 129 times with Central Arkansas leading the series 75-54.
